	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-24T04:00:03">Capita PLC provides customer and business process management services. The Company operates through nine segments: Health and Wellbeing, consisting of its health businesses; IT Services, consisting of its data and information technology managed services; Justice and Secure Services, consisting of businesses servicing the police and emergency services market, digital and gamification businesses, and parking services; Professional Services, consisting of local Government and schools software, document and information solutions, and Entrust; Property and Infrastructure, consisting of property consultancy and local Government regional partnerships; Workplace Services, consisting of human resource, and resourcing and learning businesses; Customer Management and International, consisting of customer management business; Insurance and Benefits Services, its employee benefits and insurance business, and Asset Services, consisting of shareholder solutions, and mortgage and banking solutions.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-17T13:19:05">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Capita PLC revenues increased 11% to L2.29B. Net income decreased 4% to L117M. Revenues reflect Capita Europe segment increase from L6.8M to L82.1M, Digital &amp; Software Solutions segment increase of 17% to L247.5M. Net income was offset by Administrative expenses increase of 10% to L352M (expense), Amortisation of acquired intangibles increase of 13% to L80.5M (expense).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
